# Public build-time config for the web app. ONLY VITE_-prefixed vars are
# inlined into the browser bundle, and ONLY non-secret, publicly-shippable
# values belong here — never an API key, token, or password (the bundle is
# served to every visitor). Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) to override.

# Backend origin the api-client prepends to every request.
#
# DEV: leave EMPTY. An empty base URL makes the client issue same-origin
# relative URLs (`/auth/login`) that the Vite dev proxy forwards to the compose
# backend (see vite.config.ts) — the same-origin path cookie-mode auth needs so
# the backend's SameSite=Lax cookies attach.
#
# PROD: set to the API origin ONLY if the API is served from a different origin
# than the SPA AND that origin returns credentialed CORS naming this SPA's
# origin (Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true, explicit origin, never `*`).
# The simpler prod posture is to keep it EMPTY and route `/api/*` (or the API
# paths) to the backend at the edge (e.g. CloudFront behavior) so the browser
# stays same-origin and no cross-origin CORS/cookie dance is needed. See
# docs/fragment.md's Deployment section.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=
